A method in Java is a block of code that performs a specific task. Think of it like a mini-program inside your program.

ğŸ”‘ Key Components of a Method:
Access modifier: Controls visibility (e.g., public, private)
Return type: What the method gives back (int, String, or void if nothing)
Method name: Follows camelCase naming (e.g., calculateSum)
Parameters: Optional inputs the method can use
Method body: The actual code that runs

